        <li><a href="#t11">Termination</a></li>
        <li><a href="#t12">Governing Law</a></li>
        <li><a href="#t13">Contact Us</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>

    <!-- MAIN -->
    <main class="main-content">

      <!-- 1. ACCEPTANCE -->
      <div class="t-section" id="t1">
        <div class="section-header"><span class="section-number">01</span><h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2></div>
        <p>
          By creating an account, logging into our online banking platform, using our mobile application, initiating a transfer, applying for a loan, or otherwise accessing any AgriBank Texas Regional ("AgriBank," "we," "us," or "our") service, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"), our <a href="/privacy" style="color:var(--green-600);font-weight:600;">Privacy Policy</a>, and all applicable rules, policies, and guidelines incorporated herein by reference.
        </p>
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <p><strong>Important:</strong> These Terms constitute a legally binding agreement between you and AgriBank Texas Regional. If you do not agree to any provision herein, you must immediately discontinue use of all services and close your account.</p>
        </div>
        <p>We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Material changes will be communicated via email notification, prominent website notice, or updated login screens. Continued use after modifications constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms. We encourage you to review this page periodically.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 2. ELIGIBILITY -->
      <div class="t-section" id="t2">
        <div class="section-header"><span class="section-number">02</span><h2>Account Eligibility & Requirements</h2></div>
        <p>To open or use any AgriBank service, you must meet all of the following requirements:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Age Requirement:</strong> You must be at least 18 years old and legally capable of entering into a binding contract under applicable law.</li>
          <li><strong>Identity Verification:</strong> You must provide valid, government-issued identification (driver's license, passport, or state ID), Social Security Number or Taxpayer Identification Number, and proof of address documentation.</li>
          <li><strong>Residency:</strong> You must be a resident of the United States and possess a valid U.S. mailing address. Some products may have additional geographic restrictions.</li>
          <li><strong>Credit Standing:</strong> For credit-based products (loans, lines of credit), you must satisfy our creditworthiness standards as determined solely by AgriBank.</li>
          <li><strong>No Prior Restrictions:</strong> You must not be subject to any sanctions administered by OFAC, listed on any government denied-party list, or previously barred from opening an account with us.</li>
          <li><strong>One Person, One Account:</strong> Each individual may maintain only one primary personal account unless you obtain written authorization from AgriBank.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="term-grid">
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Minimum Age</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">18 Years Old</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">ID Required</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">Government-Issued Photo ID</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Tax ID</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">SSN or ITIN Required</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Credit Check</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">Soft Pull for Accounts, Hard for Loans</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>Juvenile accounts (ages 13–17) require a custodial relationship with an eligible adult (parent or legal guardian) and are subject to separate <strong>Custodial Account Agreement</strong> terms. Business accounts require valid business registration documents, Employer Identification Number (EIN), and authorized signatory resolutions.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 3. USER RESPONSIBILITIES -->
      <div class="t-section" id="t3">
        <div class="section-header"><span class="section-number">03</span><h2>Your Responsibilities</h2></div>
        <p>By maintaining an account with AgriBank, you agree to the following responsibilities:</p>

        <h3>Accurate Information</h3>
        <p>You represent and warrant that all information provided during account opening, updates, and transactions is true, accurate, complete, and current. Failure to promptly update your contact information, employment details, or identity documents may result in account restriction or closure.</p>

        <h3>Lawful Use</h3>
        <p>You agree to use our services solely for lawful purposes and in accordance with all applicable federal, state, and local laws, including but not limited to the Bank Secrecy Act, USA PATRIOT Act, and Anti-Money Laundering regulations. You shall not use any AgriBank account for:**</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Illégal activities, terrorism financing, or money laundering</li>
          <li>Sanctions evasion or transactions with sanctioned parties or countries</li>
          <li>Fraudulent transactions, identity theft, or impersonation</li>
          <li>Unauthorized testing of systems, hacking, or attempts to compromise security</li>
          <li>Spam, phishing, or any form of electronic harassment</li>
          <li>Operating an unlicensed money services business</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Account Maintenance</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Maintain minimum balance requirements where applicable to avoid monthly maintenance fees.</li>
          <li>Review statements regularly and report discrepancies within 60 days of receipt.</li>
          <li>Keep your registered email address and phone number current for security alerts and communications.</li>
          <li>Respond promptly to verification requests from AgriBank's fraud prevention team.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="info-banner">
          <span class="info-banner-icon">📋</span>
          <p><strong>Statement Reconciliation:</strong> Under Regulation CC and UCC Article 4, you are responsible for reporting unauthorized signatures, alterations, or forged items within 30 days of receiving your statement. Failure to do so may shift liability for subsequent fraudulent activity to you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 4. SERVICES & FEES -->
      <div class="t-section" id="t4">
        <div class="section-header"><span class="section-number">04</span><h2>Banking Services & Fee Schedule</h2></div>
        <p>AgriBank offers a range of deposit, lending, and digital banking services. Below are the key product categories and associated fees. The complete Fee Schedule is available upon request, on our website, and at every branch.</p>

        <h3>Deposit Accounts</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Primary Checking:</strong> No overdraft fee (opt-in required for courtesy pay), $3/month maintenance (waived with $500 daily minimum or direct deposit)</li>
          <li><strong>Harvest Savings:</strong> 4.25% APY yield, $0 monthly fee, $25 minimum opening deposit, 6 withdrawal limit per month (federal regulation)</li>
          <li><strong>Business Operating:</strong> $8/month maintenance (waived with $5,000 average daily balance), unlimited transactions included</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Digital Services Fees</h3>
        <div class="term-grid">
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Internal Transfer</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">Free</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Domestic Wire</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">$25 per wire</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">International Wire</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">$45 per wire</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Mobile Deposit</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">Free</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Bill Pay</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">Free</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-item">
            <div class="term-item-label">Overdraft (Opt-In)</div>
            <div class="term-item-value">$35 per item</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="highlight-box">
          <p><strong>Fee Changes:</strong> AgriBank reserves the right to change fees with 30 days advance notice. If we increase fees, you may close your account without penalty before the new fees take effect. No fees will be applied retroactively to transactions already processed.</p>
        </div>

        <p>Additional ancillary fees may apply, including stop-payment fees ($25), returned item fees ($25), certified check fees ($10), cashier's check fees ($8), and expedited document delivery fees. A complete schedule is provided at account opening.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 5. TRANSFERS & PAYMENTS -->
      <div class="t-section" id="t5">
        <div class="section-header"><span class="section-number">05</span><h2>Transfers, Payments & Authorizations</h2></div>

        <h3>Electronic Fund Transfers (EFT)</h3>
        <p>All electronic transfers conducted through our platforms are governed by <strong>Regulation E</strong> (Electronic Fund Transfer Act). You authorize AgriBank to process transfers initiated through your authenticated sessions, linked devices, and authorized biometric actions. Each transfer instruction is considered irrevocable once confirmed, except as required by law.</p>

        <h3>ACH Transactions</h3>
        <p>By enrolling in ACH origination or debit authorization, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Ensure sufficient funds exist at the time of each scheduled debit.</li>
          <li>Provide at least 3 business days' notice for one-time ACH originations.</li>
          <li>Notify us immediately of any disputes regarding ACH entries within 60 calendar days of the statement date showing the entry.</li>
          <li>Not initiate ACH transactions without proper underlying authority or contractual obligation.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Wire Transfers</h3>
        <p>Wire transfer instructions are binding once confirmed. AgriBank acts only as a conduit and does not verify the accuracy of recipient information beyond basic compliance checks. Funds wired in error are recoverable only if recovered from the receiving institution, which may take 10-30 business days. AgriBank is not liable for errors originating outside our control.</p>

        <h3>Bill Pay Service</h3>
        <p>Our Bill Pay service schedules payments on behalf of customers according to entered dates and amounts. While we strive for accuracy, paper-check delivery delays, vendor processing issues, or postal service disruptions are beyond our control. Ensure sufficient funding in your designated source account before the payment due date.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 6. LOANS & CREDIT -->
      <div class="t-section" id="t6">
        <div class="section-header"><span class="section-number">06</span><h2>Loans & Credit Products</h2></div>

        <h3>Loan Origination</h3>
        <p>Approval of any loan or line of credit is discretionary and based on factors including but not limited to credit score, debt-to-income ratio, collateral value, cash flow analysis, and purpose of the loan. Pre-qualification does not constitute a commitment to lend. A formal commitment letter will be issued upon final underwriting approval.</p>

        <h3>Interest Rates & Terms</h3>
        <p>Rates are subject to change based on market conditions, credit profile, loan amount, term length, and collateral. Variable-rate loans adjust according to the specified index (typically Prime Rate or SOFR) plus our margin. Annual Percentage Rate (APR) includes interest and certain fees and represents the true cost of borrowing.</p>

        <h3>Repayment Obligation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>You are obligated to repay the full principal, accrued interest, and any applicable fees according to the agreed amortization schedule.</li>
